 \"end\": 1302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9837241777461148, \"rank\": 0.014878759475274101, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Shortly after, USADA chief Travis Tygart publicly accused WADA of trying to paper over the cracks, which led to a congressional hearing attended by the world's most decorated Olympian, Michael Phelps, last month.\", \"from\": 1422, \"to\": 1634, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1437, \"end\": 1442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USADA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 1449, \"end\": 1462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Tygart\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Travis Tygart\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Tygart\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Tygart\"}, {\"begin\": 1597, \"end\": 1605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999999863576, \"rank\": 1.3502340746582305e-11, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 1607, \"end\": 1621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0949896242386975e-28, \"text\": \"Michael Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In response, WADA has told Reuters it will be taking USADA to the Independent Compliance Review Committee (CRC) next month, putting the US's chance of hosting the 2028 Summer Games and 2034 Winter Olympics in jeopardy.\", \"from\": 1636, \"to\": 1854, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1663, \"end\": 1670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5082141267756518e-19, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 1689, \"end\": 1694, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USADA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 1702, \"end\": 1713, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.046285356161241e-15, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}, {\"begin\": 1743, \"end\": 1746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Convention_on_the_Rights_of_the_Child\", \"score\": 0.9995450671455076, \"rank\": 0.00045374249445185737, \"text\": \"CRC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Convention_on_the_Rights_of_the_Child\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Convention_on_the_Rights_of_the_Child\"}, {\"begin\": 1772, \"end\": 1774, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.968121350184875, \"rank\": 0.03230564640722946, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, 11 of the 23 swimmers who tested positive for TMZ will be competing in Paris.\", \"from\": 1855, \"to\": 1943, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1912, \"end\": 1915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 6.289032654280282e-13, \"text\": \"TMZ\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\"}, {\"begin\": 1937, \"end\": 1942, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.34877544339215e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A pitch invasioncaused a delay of nearly two hourswhen Argentina played Morocco in the men's Olympic football opener on Wednesday.\", \"from\": 1945, \"to\": 2075, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2000, \"end\": 2009, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999645887909397, \"rank\": 3.5385065661681625e-05, \"text\": \"Argentina\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2017, \"end\": 2024, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9998354420060007, \"rank\": 0.00016456756667010845, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Argentina were denied a 2-2 equaliser after a controversial VAR check ruled Cristian Medina's late goal marginally offside, keeping the score 2-1.\", \"from\": 2077, \"to\": 2223, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2077, \"end\": 2086, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999645887909397, \"rank\": 3.5385065661681625e-05, \"text\": \"Argentina\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2137, \"end\": 2140, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Video_assistant_referee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.971652970803922e-22, \"text\": \"VAR\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Video_assistant_referee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Video_assistant_referee\"}, {\"begin\": 2153, \"end\": 2168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cristian_Medina\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cristian Medina\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cristian_Medina\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cristian_Medina\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, before the decision was made, security at the Saint-Etienne Stadium had their hands full when approximately 20 fans invaded the pitch, some setting off firecrackers, after pelting Argentine players with cups and bottles.\", \"from\": 2225, \"to\": 2454, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2414, \"end\": 2423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999995821145566, \"rank\": 4.1381493707042554e-07, \"text\": \"Argentine\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Players left the pitch and headed down the tunnel for their safety but there was still time left on the clock.\", \"from\": 2455, \"to\": 2565, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Once order was restored, both teams were summoned to play the final three minutes of the game but Argentina head coach Javier Mascheranoremained appalled at how the situation was handled, branding it as \\\"the biggest circus\\\" he's ever seen.\", \"from\": 2567, \"to\": 2806, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2665, \"end\": 2674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999645887909397, \"rank\": 3.5385065661681625e-05, \"text\": \"Argentina\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2686, \"end\": 2692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cristian_Javier\", \"score\": 0.9999999999631655, \"rank\": 3.6848720770852364e-11, \"text\": \"Javier\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cristian_Javier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cristian_Javier\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He added: \\\"What happened on the pitch was a scandal, it's not a neighbourhood tournament, it's the Olympics.\\\"\", \"from\": 2808, \"to\": 2917, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, in the women's football tournament, New Zealand boss Andrew Pragnellaccused Canada of sending dronesto spy on their training sessions ahead of Thursday's match, urging Fifa to take action.\", \"from\": 2919, \"to\": 3118, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Two Canadian coaches were sent home in connection with the incident before an independent review by Canada Soccer saw head coach Bev Priestman step down from her opening match duties and apologise, then later besuspended from the Olympics entirely.\", \"from\": 3120, \"to\": 3368, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3124, \"end\": 3132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9958191961323469, \"rank\": 0.00419767888212487, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 3220, \"end\": 3233, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Soccer_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Canada Soccer\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Soccer_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Soccer_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 3249, \"end\": 3262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bev_Priestman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bev Priestman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bev_Priestman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bev_Priestman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France's largest security operation since World War II will take place this Friday at the Olympic opening ceremony, with as many as 45,000 police officers expected to be on duty.\", \"from\": 3370, \"to\": 3548, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3370, \"end\": 3376, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.999999440950134, \"rank\": 4.6146825985167665e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thousands of soldiers will join officers on the banks of the River Seine, where athletes will be taken on a 6km cultural tour around the capital.\", \"from\": 3550, \"to\": 3695, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3611, \"end\": 3622, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Additional reporting by Reuters  Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 3697, \"to\": 3960, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3721, \"end\": 3728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5082141267756518e-19, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 3781, \"end\": 3792, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.046285356161241e-15, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}]}]}"